Montréal, October 7th, 2014

V 3.1

This version of ART nouveau implements FIRE for perpendicular minimization during the activation (by Laurent Karim Béland, Oak Ridge National Lab). 

It also incorporates a number of corrections and bug fixing by Jean-François Joly (Carleton University), who revised, among other things, the implementation of Fire.

Although the basic code is taken from the ab-initio compatible version, it
is given as an exemple for empirical potential.

---------


Montréal, April 3rd, 2012
This version of ART nouveau incorporates a number of revisions, corrections, modifications and improvements made by
Eduardo Machado-Charry (CEA-Grenoble) and Laurent Karim Béland (Université de Montréal) as well as suggestions made by M.-C. Marinica (CEA-Saclay), E. Cances (École des ponts et chaussées) and F. Legoll (École des ponts et chaussées).

When using this program, please site the following papers:

G. T. Barkema et N. Mousseau, Phys. Rev. Lett. {\bf 77}, 4358 (1996). 
R. Malek et N. Mousseau, Phys. Rev. E {\bf 62}, 7723-7728 (2000). 
E. Cances, F. Legoll, M.-C. Marinica, K. Minoukadeh, and F. Willaime, J. Chem. Phys. \textbf{130}, 114711 (2009).
E. Machado-Charry, L.K. B\'eland, D. Caliste, L. Genovese, T. Deutsch, N. Mousseau and P. Pochet, J. Chem. Phys. {\bf 135}, 034102 (2011).


Details on compilation and running can be found in DOC. 

Updated versions of the code can be found on http://www.phys.umontreal.ca/~mousseau/index.php?n=Main.Logiciels

Normand Mousseau
